  "why_it_matters": [
    "The NHS has <a href='https://www.england.nhs.uk/greenernhs/a-net-zero-nhs/' target='_Blank'> committed to reducing its carbon footprint by 80% by 2028 to 2032</a>, ",
    "including a shift to lower carbon inhalers. Dry powder inhalers (DPIs) and other newer types of inhalers like soft ",
    "mist inhalers are less harmful to the environment than traditional metered dose inhalers (MDIs). </p>",
    "<p>The <a href='https://www.england.nhs.uk/long-read/national-medicines-optimisation-opportunities-2023-24/#11-improving-respiratory-outcomes-while-reducing-the-carbon-emissions-from-inhalers' target='_Blank'>",
    "NHS England National Medicines Optimisation Opportunities for 2023/24</a> identify reducing carbon emissions from inhalers as an area for improvement.</p>",
    "<p><a href='https://www.nice.org.uk/guidance/ng80/resources/inhalers-for-asthma-patient-decision-aid-pdf-6727144573' target='_Blank'>NICE has ",
    "produced a inhaler decision aid</a> to facilitiate discussion about inhaler options.</p>"
  ],
